defaultSuch measures may also encourage the terrorists.  As Jonathan Evans of MI5 said in 2010: “
defaultIn recent years we appear increasingly to have imported from the American media the assumption that terrorism is 100% preventable and that any incident that is not prevented is seen as a culpable government failure.  This is a nonsensical way to consider terrorist risk and only plays into the hands of the terrorists themselves.
default” 
defaultAyman
default al-
defaultZawahiri
default, the current leader of al-Qaida, confirmed the point in a recent message marking the 12
defaultth
default anniversary of 9/11: “
defaultWe must bleed America economically by provoking it, so that it continues its massive expenditures on security
default.”  
